bilingual.source: Animals rely on instinct to find food.
bilingual.target: 动物依靠本能寻找食物。
做决定时要相信你的本能。

bilingual.source: A mother's instinct is to protect her child.
bilingual.target: 母亲的本能是保护她的孩子。

bilingual.source: He has a strong instinct to help others.
bilingual.target: 他有一种强烈的本能去帮助别人。

bilingual.source: In danger, people's instinct is to run away.
bilingual.target: 在危险时，人们的本能是逃跑。

bilingual.source: Her instinct told her that something was wrong.
bilingual.target: 她的本能告诉她有些不对劲。

bilingual.source: Her instinct told her not to trust that person.
bilingual.target: 她的本能告诉她不要相信那个人。

bilingual.source: He has a paternal instinct to protect his children.
bilingual.target: 他有一种父亲的本能去保护他的孩子。

bilingual.source: He followed his instinct and avoided the dangerous path.
bilingual.target: 他遵循他的本能，避开了危险的道路。

bilingual.source: The homing instinct of salmon is fascinating to scientists.
bilingual.target: 鲑鱼返回原地的本能令科学家们着迷。

list.abstract: 《本能》是马克·韦布执导，艾伦·卡明、博亚娜·诺瓦科维奇、丹尼尔·英格斯等主演的电视剧，于2018年3月11日在美国播出。

瑞典组合Niki&TheDove（妮基与鸽子）算得上是近来业界的高光人物，从EP发行到一系列运作流程可以看出唱片公司对他们也很上心，今年顺利入围了BBCsoundof2012.音乐方面还是很有北欧乐队的风骨，流畅诡魅不失灵性，歌曲以及MV都会让人联想到他们的前辈与同乡，瑞典组合TheKnife+FeverRay(脑残粉儿~),就连女主唱的声音也有点儿像KarinDreijerAndersson,有时又会想到AllisonGoldfrapp,俄罗斯数码SPRAY工作室出品的朝鲜题材FPS游戏《Instinct》。游戏以04年4月朝鲜龙川列车爆炸事件为题材，并以主人公猎杀爆炸发生之后在朝鲜新益州（龙川火车站附近城市）出现的怪物为主要内容。

yingyinNormal.en: And when the eyes spot something they like, our instinct is to move closer so the other senses can investigate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而当眼睛看见喜欢的事物时，我们的本能便是靠上前，好让其他的感官也能够侦察。

yingyinNormal.en: Exactly. Exactly. For your own. For you. It's what you wanted. It's what your gut, your instinct wanted.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确实是，确实是，就为你自己，为你，是你想要的，是出于你本能的，出于直觉你就想要它。

yingyinNormal.en: Guys, one slip-up on the next event, and we're goners. So for this to work, I'm gonna need you to take every instinct you have and bury it deep deep down. Done.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大伙儿，下一关再出错就拜拜了。保险起见，你们要把任何本能深藏起来。好的。

yingyinNormal.en: And that's what worries me. I'm just operating on instinct, Ken.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那就是让我担心的事。我只是凭直觉行事，肯。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't help it. I was born with a killer instinct. That's just no excuse.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我忍不住。我生来就是杀手。这不是借口。

yingyinNormal.en: You want me to be your mole. Yes. And what makes you think you can trust me? Instinct.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你想让我当你的卧底？没错。你凭什么信任我？直觉。

yingyinNormal.en: Primates, such as ourselves, have a natural instinct to ostracize ill mannered members of the troop.
yingyinNormal.zh: 像咱们这种灵长类动物，天生就会排斥族群里不守规矩的成员。

yingyinNormal.en: Our first instinct is to seek revenge when those we love are taken from us. But that's not who we are.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当有人抢走我们爱的人，我们的第一反应是复仇，但这不是我们的天性。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, now actually, Zay brings up an interesting point. No, I don't. Riley has an instinct to accelerate the clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，其实刚才小赛提到了一个有趣的话题。我并不感兴趣。莱丽想让时间快点走。

yingyinNormal.en: You know that instinct to leap without looking that was his nature too. And in my opinion something Starfleet's lost.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他总是凭直觉做事，那是他的天赋，而且我觉得那也正是现在的星际舰队所缺乏的。

examination_example.sentence: Curiosity is often considered a good <highlight>instinct</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 好奇心通常被认为是一种良好的本能。

examination_example.sentence: Mental health has commonly been called conscience, <highlight>instinct</highlight>, wisdom, common sense, or the inner voice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 心理健康一般被称作良心、本能、智慧、常识或者心灵之音。

examination_example.sentence: But in Osborneland, your first <highlight>instinct</highlight> is to fall into dependency supported by a state only too ready to indulge your falsehood.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是在奥斯本，你的第一本能是陷入依赖，这个依赖是由一个太愿意纵容你的谎言的国家支持的。
